Uses of Package
pxd.turing.machine.impl

  • Packages that use pxd.turing.machine.impl 
    Package Description
    pxd.turing.machine.impl
    A Turing machine is an abstract machine that manipulates symbols on a strip of tape according to a table of rules; to be more exact, it is a mathematical model of computation that defines such a device.
  • Classes in pxd.turing.machine.impl used by pxd.turing.machine.impl 
    Class and Description
    Action
    Action that tells the machine what symbol to write on the tape, how to move the playhead (eg "G" for a box to the left, "D" for a box to the right), and what is the new state.
    Alphabet
    The Alphabet is the list of symbols, it contains a special blank symbol (here written as '0') and one or more other symbols.
    Cell
    The cells constituting the Tape, each cell contains a symbol from some finite alphabet.
    Head
    A head that can read and write symbols on the tape and move the tape left and right one (and only one) cell at a time.
    IdAction
    Identifier Action.
    Instructions
    Instructions is an action list.
    State
    State of the Turing Machine.
    StateRegister
    A state register that stores the state of the Turing machine.
    Symbol
    Symbols could be printed.
    Tape
    A tape divided into cells, one next to the other.
    TuringMachine
    A Turing machine is a general example of a CPU that controls all data manipulation done by a computer, with the canonical machine using sequential memory to store data.
